[{"text":"<cell id=\"cell-0\"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type># EHR Copilot — ORPO v5 Training on Colab\n\n**Goal:** Fine-tune Qwen2.5-Coder-7B-Instruct with ORPO to improve SQL generation and abstention on the EHRSQL MIMIC-III benchmark.\n\n**Target:** RS(10) ≥ 0.813 (EHRSQL 2024 leaderboard top score — LG AI / KAIST)\n\n**Current best (ORPO v4 Colab, full run):** RS(10) = 0.477, correct_answers = 572/1198, wrong_on_unanswerable = 28\n\n**Recommended runtime:** A100 40GB (Runtime → Change runtime type → A100)\n\n---\n\n## What's fixed in v5 (vs v4 — three fundamental bugs fixed)\n\n| | v4 | v5 |\n|---|---|---|\n| Starting adapter | ORPO v3 | ORPO v4 (full Colab run, 327/327 steps) |\n| System prompt | Mismatched (training ≠ eval) | Unified — identical in training + eval |\n| Training signal | String-diff on broken MIMIC-III gold SQL | Execution-verified — only valid-gold questions used |\n| Unanswerable rejected | Random gold SQL | Model's own inference output (stronger signal) |\n| Gold SQL canonicalization | 4 renames only | 8 remaps + correlated subqueries (21% → 31% valid) |\n| EX scoring | False positives from error==error match | Fixed: gold error → no credit |\n| LR | 5e-6 | 2e-6 (already converged) |\n\n**Root causes fixed:**\n- **False positive scoring bug:** `frozenset()==frozenset()` counted error+error as \"correct\" — inflated EX by ~56%\n- **Backwards training signal:** String-diff against broken MIMIC-III gold SQL meant model was trained to prefer SQL that can't execute on MIMIC-IV-Demo\n- **Missing schema remaps:** Only 4 of 10+ column differences were handled; now 21%→31% of gold SQL executes\n\n---\n\n## Before you start\n\nUpload `EHRCopilot_colab_data.zip` to your Google Drive at:\n\n```\nMyDrive/EHRCopilot/EHRCopilot_colab_data.zip\n```\n\nThe v5 zip contains: SQLite DB, EHRSQL splits, **v5 ORPO pairs** (valid-gold-only), BGE embeddings, template classifier, **ORPO v4 Colab adapter**, and updated source (all bug fixes).\n\n---\n\n## Steps\n1. ▶ **Cell 1** — check GPU\n2. ▶ **Cell 2** — install dependencies (~3 min)\n3. ▶ **Cell 3** — mount Drive + extract data zip\n4. ▶ **Cell 4** — verify all files present\n5. ▶ **Cell 5** — detect GPU and set batch config\n6. ▶ **Cell 6** — run ORPO v5 training (~5–7 hrs A100)\n7. ▶ **Cell 7** — save adapter to Google Drive\n8. ▶ **Cell 8** *(optional)* — RAGAS retrieval eval (92.7% recall+precision)\n9. ▶ **Cell 9** *(optional)* — full eval + RS(10) score</cell id=\"cell-0\">\n<cell id=\"cell-1\"># ── Cell 1: Check GPU ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nimport subprocess, torch\n\nr = subprocess.run(['nvidia-smi', '--query-gpu=name,memory.total,memory.free',\n                    '--format=csv,noheader'], capture_output=True, text=True)\nprint('GPU:', r.stdout.strip())\nprint(f'PyTorch: {torch.__version__}  |  CUDA: {torch.cuda.is_available()}')\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    print(f'Device: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}')\n    print(f'VRAM:   {torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB')</cell id=\"cell-1\">\n<cell id=\"cell-2\"># ── Cell 2: Install dependencies (~3 min) ─────────────────────────────────\n!pip install -q \"unsloth[colab-new] @ git+https://github.com/unslothai/unsloth.git\"\n!pip install -q \\\n    \"trl>=0.9.0\" \"peft>=0.11.0\" \"bitsandbytes>=0.43.0\" \\\n    \"accelerate>=0.30.0\" \"transformers>=4.45.0\" \\\n    \"datasets>=2.19.0\" \"huggingface-hub>=0.23.0\" \\\n    \"sentence-transformers>=2.7.0\" \"rank-bm25>=0.2.2\" \\\n    \"scikit-learn>=1.4.0\" \"joblib>=1.3.0\"\nprint('All dependencies installed.')</cell id=\"cell-2\">\n<cell id=\"cell-3\"># ── Cell 3: Mount Drive + extract data zip ────────────────────────────────\nfrom google.colab import drive\nimport zipfile, os\n\ndrive.mount('/content/drive')\n\nDRIVE_ZIP = '/content/drive/MyDrive/EHRCopilot/EHRCopilot_colab_data.zip'\nos.chdir('/content')\n\nif not os.path.exists(DRIVE_ZIP):\n    raise FileNotFoundError(\n        f'Not found: {DRIVE_ZIP}\\n'\n        'Upload EHRCopilot_colab_data.zip to MyDrive/EHRCopilot/ and rerun.'\n    )\n\nsize_mb = os.path.getsize(DRIVE_ZIP) / 1024 / 1024\nprint(f'Found {DRIVE_ZIP}  ({size_mb:.0f} MB)')\nprint('Extracting ...')\n\nwith zipfile.ZipFile(DRIVE_ZIP) as zf:\n    zf.extractall('/content')\n\nprint('Done.')</cell id=\"cell-3\">\n<cell id=\"cell-4\"># ── Cell 4: Verify all files ───────────────────────────────────────────────\nimport os, sys, json\n\nsys.path.insert(0, '/content/src')\nos.environ['PYTHONPATH'] = '/content/src'\nos.environ['TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM'] = 'false'\n\nchecks = [\n    ('data/mimic_iv_demo.db',                                               'SQLite DB'),\n    ('data/ehrsql/orpo_v5_pairs.jsonl',                                     'ORPO v5 training pairs'),\n    ('data/ehrsql/template_classifier.pkl',                                  'Template classifier'),\n    ('data/ehrsql/train_embeddings_bge_large.npy',                          'BGE-large embeddings'),\n    ('data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/train.json',                             'EHRSQL train split'),\n    ('data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/valid.json',                             'EHRSQL valid split'),\n    ('data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/test.json',                              'EHRSQL test split'),\n    ('checkpoints/orpo_v4_colab/adapter_final/adapter_model.safetensors',   'ORPO v4 Colab adapter'),\n    ('src/ehrcopilot/finetune/abstention_dpo.py',                           'Training script'),\n    ('src/ehrcopilot/eval/harness.py',                                       'Eval harness (v5 fixes)'),\n]\n\nprint('File check:')\nall_ok = True\nfor path, desc in checks:\n    ok = os.path.exists(path)\n    size = f'  ({os.path.getsize(path)/1024/1024:.0f} MB)' if ok else ''\n    print(f'  {\"OK\" if ok else \"MISSING\"}  {path}{size}  — {desc}')\n    if not ok:\n        all_ok = False\n\nif all_ok:\n    pairs = [json.loads(l) for l in open('data/ehrsql/orpo_v5_pairs.jsonl')]\n    n_ans   = sum(1 for p in pairs if p.get('is_answerable', True))\n    n_unans = sum(1 for p in pairs if not p.get('is_answerable', True))\n    print(f'\\nORPO v5 pairs: {len(pairs)} total  ({n_ans} SQL quality + {n_unans} abstention)')\n    print('  SQL pairs are ONLY from questions where gold SQL executes with real data on MIMIC-IV-Demo.')\n    print('  This is the key fix vs v4 — no more backwards training signal from broken gold SQL.')\n    print('\\nAll files present — ready to train!')\nelse:\n    print('\\nSome files missing — check the zip contents.')</cell id=\"cell-4\">\n<cell id=\"cell-5\"># ── Cell 5: Detect GPU and set batch config ────────────────────────────────\nimport os, sys, torch\n\nos.chdir('/content')\nsys.path.insert(0, '/content/src')\nos.environ['PYTHONPATH'] = '/content/src'\nos.environ['TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM'] = 'false'\n\ngpu_name = torch.cuda.get_device_name(0) if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'CPU'\nvram_gb  = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9 if torch.cuda.is_available() else 0\nprint(f'GPU: {gpu_name}  ({vram_gb:.1f} GB VRAM)')\n\nif vram_gb >= 35:    # A100 40GB\n    BATCH_SIZE, GRAD_ACCUM, MAX_LENGTH = 4, 4, 1536\nelif vram_gb >= 20:  # A100 20GB / L4\n    BATCH_SIZE, GRAD_ACCUM, MAX_LENGTH = 2, 8, 1536\nelse:                # T4 16GB\n    BATCH_SIZE, GRAD_ACCUM, MAX_LENGTH = 1, 16, 1024\n\nprint(f'batch={BATCH_SIZE}  grad_accum={GRAD_ACCUM}  max_length={MAX_LENGTH}')\nprint(f'Effective batch size: {BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM}  (target: 16)')</cell id=\"cell-5\">\n<cell id=\"cell-6\"># ── Cell 6: Run ORPO v5 training ───────────────────────────────────────────\n# Starting from ORPO v4 Colab adapter. Key fixes vs v4:\n#   - Unified system prompt (training now matches eval)\n#   - Only valid-gold pairs (gold SQL executes with real data on our DB)\n#   - Unanswerable rejected = model's own inference output\n#   - LR=2e-6 (already well-converged)\n# A100 40GB: ~5-7 hrs  |  T4 16GB: ~20-28 hrs\n\nimport subprocess, sys, os\n\ncmd = [\n    sys.executable, '-m', 'ehrcopilot.finetune.abstention_dpo',\n    '--pairs',      'data/ehrsql/orpo_v5_pairs.jsonl',\n    '--adapter',    'checkpoints/orpo_v4_colab/adapter_final',\n    '--output',     'checkpoints/orpo_v5',\n    '--epochs',     '1',\n    '--lr',         '2e-6',\n    '--max-length', str(MAX_LENGTH),\n]\n\nprint('Command:', ' '.join(cmd))\nprint('-' * 60)\n\nproc = subprocess.Popen(\n    cmd,\n    stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True,\n    env={**os.environ, 'PYTHONPATH': '/content/src', 'TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM': 'false'},\n)\nfor line in proc.stdout:\n    print(line, end='', flush=True)\nproc.wait()\nprint(f'\\nExit code: {proc.returncode}')</cell id=\"cell-6\">\n<cell id=\"cell-7\"># ── Cell 7: Save ORPO v5 adapter to Google Drive ──────────────────────────\nimport shutil, os\n\nSRC = '/content/checkpoints/orpo_v5'\nDST = '/content/drive/MyDrive/EHRCopilot/checkpoints/orpo_v5'\n\nif os.path.exists(SRC):\n    if os.path.exists(DST):\n        shutil.rmtree(DST)\n    shutil.copytree(SRC, DST)\n    print(f'ORPO v5 adapter saved to: {DST}')\n    for f in os.listdir(f'{DST}/adapter_final'):\n        size_mb = os.path.getsize(f'{DST}/adapter_final/{f}') / 1024 / 1024\n        print(f'  {f}  ({size_mb:.0f} MB)')\nelse:\n    print('No checkpoint at', SRC, '— did training complete?')</cell id=\"cell-7\">\n<cell id=\"cell-8\"># ── Cell 8 (optional): RAGAS retrieval eval ────────────────────────────────\n# Confirms template retrieval quality: target Recall@2 >= 90%, Precision@2 >= 90%.\n# Expected: ~92.7% on both (pre-validated locally).\n\nimport subprocess, sys\n\nresult = subprocess.run([\n    sys.executable, '-m', 'ehrcopilot.eval.rag_eval',\n    '--train',             'data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/train.json',\n    '--test',              'data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/test.json',\n    '--mode',              'template',\n    '--embed-cache',       'data/ehrsql/train_embeddings_bge_large.npy',\n    '--classifier-cache',  'data/ehrsql/template_classifier.pkl',\n    '--output',            'rag_eval_results.json',\n    '--k',                 '1,2,5',\n], capture_output=True, text=True,\n   env={**os.environ, 'PYTHONPATH': '/content/src'})\n\nprint(result.stdout)\nif result.returncode != 0:\n    print('STDERR:', result.stderr[-500:])</cell id=\"cell-8\">\n<cell id=\"cell-9\"># ── Cell 9 (optional): Full eval — RS(N) scoring ─────────────────────────\n# SQL generation → execution-guided repair → RS(0)/RS(5)/RS(10) scoring.\n# Uses template retrieval (92.7% precision) for 2-shot examples.\n# A100: ~1.5-2 hrs  |  T4: ~4-6 hrs\n#\n# Fixed vs v4 eval:\n#   - EX_valid_gold: EX only on questions where gold SQL returns real data (true signal)\n#   - gold_exec_valid/empty/error: shows how many questions are actually evaluable on our DB\n#   - No false positives from error==error matching\n\nimport subprocess, sys, json, os\n\nADAPTER = 'checkpoints/orpo_v5/adapter_final'\nOUTPUT  = 'orpo_v5_eval_results.json'\n\nproc = subprocess.Popen([\n    sys.executable, '-m', 'ehrcopilot.eval.harness',\n    'data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/test.json',\n    '--model',            ADAPTER,\n    '--output',           OUTPUT,\n    '--save-predictions', 'orpo_v5_predictions.jsonl',\n    '--repair',\n    '--few-shot',         'data/ehrsql/ehrsql/mimic_iii/train.json',\n    '--retrieval-mode',   'template',\n    '--classifier-cache', 'data/ehrsql/template_classifier.pkl',\n    '--embed-cache',      'data/ehrsql/train_embeddings_bge_large.npy',\n], stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True,\n   env={**os.environ, 'PYTHONPATH': '/content/src', 'TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM': 'false'})\n\nfor line in proc.stdout:\n    print(line, end='', flush=True)\nproc.wait()\n\nif os.path.exists(OUTPUT):\n    r = json.load(open(OUTPUT))\n    print('\\n' + '='*60)\n    print('  COMPETITION METRIC (MIMIC-III DB required for accurate measurement)')\n    print(f'  EX:                      {r.get(\"EX\", 0):.4f}  (answerable accuracy, all 1198 questions)')\n    print(f'  RS(10):                  {r.get(\"RS(10)\", 0):.4f}   (target ≥ 0.813)')\n    print()\n    print('  LOCAL SIGNAL (trustworthy on MIMIC-IV-Demo)')\n    print(f'  EX_valid_gold:           {r.get(\"EX_valid_gold\", 0):.4f}  (accuracy on {r.get(\"gold_exec_valid\", 0)} questions where gold SQL has real data)')\n    print(f'  gold_exec_valid:         {r.get(\"gold_exec_valid\", 0)} / 1198  (questions with evaluable gold SQL)')\n    print(f'  gold_exec_empty:         {r.get(\"gold_exec_empty\", 0)} / 1198  (gold runs but patient not in demo DB)')\n    print(f'  gold_exec_error:         {r.get(\"gold_exec_error\", 0)} / 1198  (gold fails — missing MIMIC-III table/column)')\n    print()\n    print('  ABSTENTION QUALITY')\n    print(f'  correct_answers:         {r.get(\"correct_answers\", 0)} / 1198')\n    print(f'  wrong_on_unanswerable:   {r.get(\"wrong_answers_on_unanswerable\", 0)} / 588  (each costs 10 RS pts; target ≤ 5)')\n    print(f'  correct_abstentions:     {r.get(\"correct_abstentions\", 0)} / 588')\n    print('='*60)\n    print()\n    print('  Predictions saved to: orpo_v5_predictions.jsonl')\n    print('  Copy to Drive: shutil.copy(\"orpo_v5_predictions.jsonl\", \"/content/drive/MyDrive/EHRCopilot/\")')</cell id=\"cell-9\">","type":"text"}]
